attributes.attribute: With traditional GUI test automation, you have to decide with which attribute you want to identify a component. If your chosen attribute changes, your test fails although the application still works. With retest you don't need to decide for an attribute ... you simply use them all. This redundancy would normally mean a lot of additional effort. But not with retest. Maintaining your test happens with a single click.
